title: For Sale:  1943 wartime Sako M39
postcontent: Beautiful rifle, bluing is worn but shoots great. nice tiger striping on parts of the stock. Field armory repaired original buttstock and rarer reinforced joint splices on butt. Original wartime stock, I have known people who've had the uncracked basically new M39's and the stocks cracked because it's pretty normal for the series of rifle due to the nature of the grain pattern of wood - the armory repaired version is actually sturdier and better reinforced for shooting, finding them with original armory repairs is uncommon, and is considered higher end than an unrepaired one, or civilian repair. What makes this rifle more rare is that it was partially blued in the less common burgundy bluing color under the stock, I believe the rest was removed/polished by conscripts post-war to reblue the rifle. The rifle would have probably then gotten a post-war stock and reblued but didn't.This rifle also includes a very rare SKY civil guard marked sling.
